-- SJM Drops as Term Sheet Shows Investors Sell Stock
-- B y   F o x   H u
-- 2010-11-09T07:08:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/sjm-drops-as-term-sheet-shows-investors-seek-to-sell-stock.html
SJM Holdings Ltd. , Asia’s biggest
listed casino operator,  slid  as much as 3.5 percent, reversing
earlier gains, as a sale document showed investors seek to raise
as much as HK$821 million ($106 million) selling its stock.  SJM  traded at HK$12, down by 1.3 percent, as of 2:58 p.m.
Hong Kong time. The casino operator earlier surged as much as
4.4 percent.  The casino operator’s shareholders are offering 67 million
shares at HK$11.75 to HK$12.25, according to a copy of a term
sheet sent to investors today.  Deutsche Bank AG  is managing the
sale, the document showed.  SJM , controlled by Macau billionaire  Stanley Ho , has almost
tripled this year in Hong Kong trading as total gambling revenue
in the former Portuguese colony have surged 59 percent so far
this year. Macau is the only place in China where casinos are
legal.  Profit at  SJM  surged more than fivefold to HK$2.43 billion
first nine months of this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fox Hu in Hong Kong at 
